1 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 6-207, as
2 amended by Section 70, Chapter 282, O.S.L. 2022 (47 O.S. Supp. 2024,
3 Section 6-207), is amended to read as follows:
4 Section 6-207. Whenever Service Oklahoma is furnished with
5 information or, from the records on file in Service Oklahoma, it is
6 established that the holder of a driver license is afflicted with a
7 physical disease with a history of seizures, or mental disease, or
8 momentary lapses of consciousness or any other ailment which may
9 result in temporary loss of control or partial control of a motor
10 vehicle, Service Oklahoma may, in its discretion, execute an order
11 of cancellation of any driver license issued to such individual, or,
12 should such information be available at the time of application for
13 a driver license, Service Oklahoma may execute an order denying the
14 issuance of said license to any such individual and shall cause any
15 such license that may have been issued to be picked up or to be
16 delivered to Service Oklahoma as specified for other such orders.
17 Every physician or surgeon, including doctors of medicine and
18 osteopathy, examining, attending or treating an individual for any
19 illness or injury that would impair the ability of the individual in
20 any manner as to affect the performance of the person to operate a
21 motor vehicle, may make a written report of the diagnosis to Service
22 Oklahoma. Any person who is diagnosed with a disorder that causes a
23 momentary lapse of consciousness that would impair the ability of
24 the individual in any manner as to affect the performance of the
