1 pers on to operate a motor vehicle shall report his or her diagnosis
2 to Service Oklahoma. Service Oklahoma may, in its discretion,
3 suspend or cancel the license of such person for such period of time
4 as in its judgment is justified.
5 In addition thereto, any person or physician or any medical
6 personnel participating in good faith and without negligence or
7 malicious intent in making of a report pursuant to this act shall
8 have the immunity from civil liability that might otherwise be
9 incurred or imposed. Any such participant shall have the same
10 immunity with respect to participation in any judicial proceeding
11 resulting from such report.
12 Provided further that, in any proceeding resulting from a report
13 made pursuant to this act or in any proceeding where such a report
14 or any contents thereof are sought to be introduced in evidence,
15 such report or contents or any other fact or facts related thereto,
16 or the condition of the individual who is the subject of the report
17 shall only be admitted in evidence in actions regarding the
18 revocation, suspension, cancellation or denial of the subject's
19 driver's license and. The report shall not be considered to be a
20 public record provided that the report shall not be excluded on the
21 ground that the matter is or may be the subject of a physician-
22 patient privilege or similar privilege or rule against disclosure.
